description: Every county in Georgia has certified its general election results. There had been concerns about election certification, but with Donald Trump's victory, those worries have largely gone away.
title: Georgia counties certify the election, as fraud claims dissipate after Trump win

description: Samantha Harvey has won the 2024 Booker Prize for her science fiction novel Orbital. The novel follows six international astronauts as they orbit the Earth for one day of their nine-month space mission.
title: 'Orbital' by Samantha Harvey wins 2024 Booker Prize

description: State house elections this fall will determine whether Minnesota continues to pass progressive laws on abortion and health care or if the GOP can stem the trend led by Gov. Tim Walz.
title: MINN GOP TRIES FOR DIVIDED GOVERNMENT:

description: A federal judge sentenced Jack Teixeira, a Massachusetts Air National Guard member, to prison after he pleaded guilty to leaking highly classified military documents about the war in Ukraine.
title: Pentagon secrets leaker Jack Teixeira is sentenced to 15 years in prison

description: The Biden administration issued a new fee on climate-warming methane pollution, but the EPA regulation faces an uncertain future under President-elect Trump
title: A methane pollution fee on oil and gas faces a cloudy future under Trump

description: President-elect Donald Trump is building his team, filling out cabinet and advisory roles with those considered to be fierce loyalists. Here's how his new administration is taking shape.
title: Here's who Trump has picked as cabinet members and key advisers

description: Abortion restrictions, taxes and everyday issues are among the laws Kansas Republicans have imposed through their "supermajority" in the Legislature. Democrats aim to end its reign.
title: Democrats in Kansas hope to end GOP supermajority

description: The Supreme Court dealt a major legal blow to former White House Chief of Staff Mark Meadows on Tuesday, refusing to move the Georgia election interference charges against him to federal court.
title: Supreme Court refuses legal lifesaver for former Trump chief of staff

description: Israel's Defense Minister was fired last week by Prime Minster Benjamin Netanyahu who said that trust had "eroded" between them. The now former defense minister met with families of Israeli hostages held in Gaza and gave his thoughts on what Israel can still achieve in Gaza. We hear what was said.
title: A Frank Assessment of Israel's Goals in Gaza From the Former Defense Minister

description: The three 1980s staples are new National Toy Hall of Fame inductees. Hess Toy Trucks, the Pokémon Trading Card Game, the trampoline, and balloons were among the finalists.
title: My Little Pony, Transformers, Phase 10  join the National Toy Hall of Fame

description: The jury also decided to hold a Virginia-based military contractor responsible for contributing to the torture and mistreatment of detainees at the notorious Iraqi prison two decades ago.
title: A U.S. jury awards former Iraqi detainees $42 million for Abu Ghraib prison abuse

description: In the midst of the Israel-Hamas war, President-elect Donald Trump announced he will nominate Huckabee, a loyalist and former Republican governor, to serve in the key post as ambassador to Israel.
title: Trump to name former Arkansas Gov. Mike Huckabee as ambassador to Israel

description: Journalist Annie Lowrey has a rare disease that causes a near-constant itch that doesn't respond to most treatments. She likens the itchiness to a car alarm: "You can't stop thinking about it."
title: Chronic itch is miserable. Scientists are just scratching the surface

description: The National Institutes of Health, the crown jewel of biomedical research in the U.S., could face big changes under the new Trump administration, some fueled by pandemic-era criticisms of the agency.
title: With Trump coming into power, the NIH is in the crosshairs

description: Authorities say Nicholas Hamlett killed a man in Tennessee in an attempt to steal his identity, and reported it to police as a bear attack. He was arrested in South Carolina after a weekslong manhunt.
title: A man told 911 a bear chased him off a cliff. Weeks later, he was arrested for murder

description: A man who authorities said was upset over his divorce settlement rammed his car into a crowd of people exercising at a sports complex in southern China, police said.
title: A man drove his car into a crowd in southern China, killing 35

description: The original 2021 ruling ordered Shell to cut its carbon emissions by 45% by 2030 compared to 2019 levels. The appeals court said there is "insufficient consensus" on a specific reduction percentage.
title: Dutch appeals court overturns landmark climate ruling against Shell

description: Participant reported relief from chronic low back pain and reduced need for pain-relief medications.
title: Online yoga classes prove helpful for back pain in new study

description: Sudan's civil war has displaced 10 million citizens. Here are profiles of two young people from the most vulnerable groups: an unaccompanied minor caring for twin brothers, a woman who was raped.
title: They're the most vulnerable of refugees. And they're remarkably resilient

description: Gallego led in the polls for much of his race against Kari Lake, a MAGA firebrand who's yet to concede her 2022 gubernatorial loss.
title: Ruben Gallego defeats Kari Lake in Arizona Senate race

description: Where did Democrats go wrong with men this election? How did Republicans win them over, and how might Democrats work to win some of them back?NPR's Michel Martin speaks with Aaron Smith of the Young Men Research Initiative and John Della Volpe with the Harvard Kennedy School Institute of Politics.
title: Young men helped Trump retake the White House -- a trend years in the making

description: Voters really don't like inflation. In fact, whenever there's a sustained jump in the cost of living, the party in power often pays a price.
title: Why high prices toppled Democrats -- and other governments around the world

description: The Sing Sing maximum security prison in New York held its first-ever film festival recently, with incarcerated men invited to judge the five entries.
title: Inside this maximum security prison, a film festival proves 'a little bit healing'

description: President Biden used to tell world leaders "America is back," implying the Trump era's go-it-alone ethos was a one-term blip. But Biden needs a new line for this week's APEC and G20 summits.
title: Trump is back: how Biden will tweak his 'America's back' message at APEC and the G20

description: Revered abolitionist Harriet Tubman, who was the first woman to oversee an American military action during a time of war, was posthumously awarded the rank of general on Monday.
title: Harriet Tubman posthumously named a general in Veterans Day ceremony

description: An estimated 200,000 people, many of them Indigenous Māori, suffered abuse in New Zealand's foster and faith-based care over a period of seven decades
title: New Zealand's leader apologizes to survivors of abuse in state and church care

description: John Robinson, the veteran football coach who enjoyed many years of success at the University of Southern California and with the Los Angeles Rams, has died. He was 89.
title: John Robinson, successful football coach at USC and with the LA Rams, has died at 89
